Dear residents and friends, updating that the event in Kfar Aza is not over yet. There are still terrorists in several locations, so it's most important to stay in the shelter. For any noise, send CENSORED a message with the location of the house and what you hear.
The Tzachi team has been intensively handling all events since 7:15 in the morning and receiving reports of wounded and disconnected people.
We are in close and continuous contact with the army in the kibbutz. Currently, there is a beginning of evacuation of severely wounded, wounded children, children. Everything according to the army's prioritization.
I won't tell you that the situation is good. I believe in transparency, and most of you are in the heart of the matter and know that the situation is difficult and the injuries are not simple. There are also house fires and complex events.
I and others on the team have been receiving requests from all of you for hours and passing them on to the army and those who can provide information and help. Unfortunately, we lack a lot of information at this stage.
We promise to update when we know more, in real-time, and in the meantime, we are working around the clock to do everything possible, given the circumstances. Yours, CENSORED
